fields.value: Census of population and housing, 1970 summary statistic file 1

authorName.value: Data Use and Access Laboratories (DUALabs), Arlington, Va.

dsDescriptionValue.value:
"The data are presented in 55 tables containing 400 population and housing data cells. Population items included are age, race, sex, marital status, and relationship to head of household. Cross-tabulations of population items include age and sex, and Negro and other races (except White) by age and sex. Housing items include vacancy status, tenure, rent value, plumbing facilities, etc. Housing items cross- tabulated include aggregate number of persons by tenure, and race of head and families b y plumbing facilities. This file is also known as ""First Count."""

File A gives summaries for each State and for each enumeration district or block group. File B provides summaries for the States, counties, minor civil divisions (MCD's) or census county divisions, places, and congressional districts.

Data contained in the files pertain to the date of the census, April 1, 1970
